Package edu.umb.cs682.ecom.backend.controllers

Class UserController

  • Object
    • UserController
  • @CrossOrigin(origins="*",
             maxAge=3600L)
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/api/user")
public class UserController
extends Object
    UserController manages requests from the frontend related to Users. The methods in this class directly correspond to the functions in the UserService.js frontend class.

      • getMyStuff

        @GetMapping("/mystuff")
@PreAuthorize("@tokenWhitelistService.containsToken(authentication) and hasRole(\'CUSTOMER\')")
public ProfileResponse getMyStuff()
        Gets the personalized content associated with the current user.

        The current user information is extracted from the authentication token used to make this request. Only users with the role 'CUSTOMER' have access to this mapping.

        The corresponding frontend requester is the getMyStuff() function in the UserService.js class.

        NOTE: This feature is incomplete and currently returns the same data as the getProfile() method.
        Returns:
        the ProfileResponse object corresponding to the current user

        The corresponding frontend requester is the addToCart() function in the UserService.js class.

        Parameters:

        Returns:

      • proceedToCheckout

        @PostMapping("/profile/checkout")
@PreAuthorize("@tokenWhitelistService.containsToken(authentication) and hasRole(\'CUSTOMER\')")
public PreOrderResponse proceedToCheckout​(@Valid @RequestBody
                                          @Valid CheckoutRequest request)
        Processes a user's request to begin the checkout process. Only users with the 'CUSTOMER' role have access to this mapping.

        The CheckoutRequest argument to this method should contain the current user's username, cart details, and a calculated subtotal. The corresponding details are retrieved from the database and compared against the CheckoutRequest for consistency. An exception is thrown if values don't match.

        A temporary PreOrder containing all details relevant to the order is generated and returned to the frontend. more text

        The corresponding frontend requester is the proceedToCheckout() function in the UserService.js class.

        WARNING: This implementation uses float for currency, which is prone to rounding errors. As such, the subtotal amount is not validated with the backend and is simply recalculated to prevent extraneous thrown exceptions. This can be fixed in future releases of this software product.

        NOTE: This feature is incomplete. Currently, arbitrary taxes and shipping charges are applied to the order in place of real tax and shipping charges. This should be fixed in future iterations of this software product.
        Parameters:
        request - the CheckoutRequest containing the username and cart details
        Returns:
        the PreOrderResponse object containing a temporary order for the cart items

      • placeOrder

        @PostMapping("/profile/placeorder")
@PreAuthorize("@tokenWhitelistService.containsToken(authentication) and hasRole(\'CUSTOMER\')")
public OrderResponse placeOrder​(@Valid @RequestBody
                                @Valid PlaceOrderRequest request)
        Processes an order on behalf of the user, if the PreOrder has not expired.

        The PlaceOrderRequest contains the PreOrder provided in the proceedToCheckout(edu.umb.cs682.ecom.backend.payload.request.CheckoutRequest) method, which is converted into an Order and returned to the frontend in an OrderResponse.

        The corresponding frontend requester is the placeOrder() function in the UserService.js class.

        WARNING: This feature is incomplete. Currently, if the PreOrder has expired, this method will throw an exception. Future implementations of this software product will appropriately handle expired PreOrders.

        Parameters:
        request - the PlaceOrderRequest containing the order details
        Returns:
        the OrderResponse which contains the user's Order
